Case description : Initial report received on 11-May-2022 from EMA Eudravigilance ICSR search. Agency report: FR-AFSSAPS-RS20221 448.
Report received by phone call by a health professional.

The case concerned an 81-year-old male patient.

Medical history:

- disseminated lupus erythematosus

- coronary spastic angina

- deep vein thrombosis

- hepatic cyst

- pancreatic cyst

- intraductal papillary mucinous neoplasm

- tendinitis

- senile macular degeneration

- Raynaud's phenomenon

Suspected drugs:

- methotrexate (unspecified trade name) from 05-Apr-2022 to 18-Apr-2022, at 15 mg daily by oral route for disseminated lupus erythematosus
Adverse events:

- 05-Apr-2022: prescribing error, lasted 13 days

outcome: resolving

- 05-Apr-2022: intake of weekly dose more frequently for 13 days
outcome: resolving

- 16-Apr-2022: occurrence of pancytopenia

outcome: resolving

Patient in nursing home from end Mar-2022
